caption: Gainsbourg's music was an opportunity for cinema Gainsbourg had the appearance of a dilettante, of someone who doesn't care. In fact, it was enough to see him conduct a recording to realize what an extremely inspired and wonderfully professional musician he was.
Not to be missed during your visit to the cemetery

Moment of contemplation for a genius of words and music. Remember to leave a cigarette and a good validated metro ticket in tribute to the Lilas puncher. Happy to see that there are still people who have not forgotten him and remember the meaning of the immense heritage he left us. Always a bit of sadness and emotion. R.I.P.

A tomb in his image. Great gentleman.
Moving to be in front of Ginsbar.
